##Across the epidemic area: Wuhan "caring driver" 12 hours a day

I-CAIJING

CAIJING magazine official Wechat. "CAIJING" magazine, sponsored by the China Securities Market Research Center, was first published in 1998, adhering to the news concept of "independence, exclusiveness and originality" , and is known for authoritative, impartial and professional reporting, it is a must-read publication for policy-makers, researchers and managers in the field of politics and economics.

The following article was written by Liu Yiqin, an 11-member finance and economics expert

The Spring Chill in Wuhan is chilly, and the epidemic is still spreading. But also because of the fight against the epidemic, did not know the driver and the doctor, to achieve an unprecedented tacit understanding. "thank you" and "refuels" , is each time they meet and separate the sign

By Liu Yiqin, special correspondent, Caijing, Wuhan | edited by Xie Lirong

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Photo 1: A caring driver on the road, by Liu Yiqin

At 6 am on February 2, Wuhan was still shrouded in morning light, and Duchuan was ready to set out. He is a Didi taxi driver, today's first "order" is to send a doctor to work.

Duchuan's last daily order on the Didi Platform was for a taxi on the evening of January 24 when a doctor went home from work. The doctor told him that the main means of transportation had been suspended and that the hardest thing was for them, that residents could continue to take leave or be quarantined at home, and that medical staff had to be on duty every day.

The doctor's appointment was at 7:30 a.m. , and Du arrived at the gate of the Community Service Center at 7:00 a.m. . He also had to thoroughly sterilize the vehicle, then take photos and clock in.

On January 23, private cars were banned in Wuhan; on January 24, Didi Platform suspended its Travel Service in Wuhan; and on January 25, Didi summoned 1,336 online ride-hailing drivers to form a "community protection team" to be unified by the community. At the same time, Didi organized more than 200 drivers to set up a "medical security convoy" to provide travel services for medical staff.

Du Chuan is the first to join the community security team of "caring drivers. ". He is a native of Wuhan, served as a soldier, after the army to a business boss as a driver. When the company closed down, he became a taxi driver for Didi.

Transport is a city's blood, responsible for connecting every corner of the city. At the end of 2019, there were 260 million cars in China, with more than 2 million in 30 cities, according to public figures. Wuhan was one of them, with about 3 million.

Wuhan also has 10 subway lines and more than 400 bus lines, as well as the city's unique ferry across the river. But the city's ties have been put on hold since the outbreak broke out.

Thousands of "caring drivers" , like Du Chuan, have taken over the baton of supporting the basic operation of the super-city, providing the most basic guarantee for Wuhan to fight the epidemic. They risked their lives in the hope that they would contribute to the recovery of the epidemic, but not for nothing. February 2 this day, "Caijing" reporter in Wuhan Tracking Report, Duchuan received the most one sentence is: "thank you, hard

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Driver du Chuan disinfects and ventilates a vehicle. Photo by Liu Yiqin

February 2nd, 7:30 am: All good news

Today's first stop is Hankow Hospital district of central war zone General Hospital, where Du Chuan sent a doctor to work. The doctor used a community support convoy for the first time and had to ask a colleague for help with the traffic control.

On weekdays, this time is the morning rush hour in Wuhan, but today's Wuhan, the road traffic is very few, all the way unimpeded.

Doctor passengers are not on line one, but on line two, ready to go to war. He told the CAIJING reporter, the hospital's materials are very tight, they as second-line medical staff, the use of some simple protective equipment, professional materials are saved for first-line colleagues.

The doctor also came with good news. He learned that the number of severe cases of new crown pneumonia in Wuhan is not very high. He learned a few days ago that the number is about 500-600, most of the patients are still suffering from mild cases, we don't have the latest data yet.

After arriving at his destination, Duchuan hopes to take orders again on Didi's platform. Didi has launched a new feature in the APP, with first-line Hospital staff opening up the ability to call a car on Didi. But there have been no new orders, said Du Chuan, the morning shift doctors are very early to work, this time should have arrived at the hospital, "as long as the order issued by the medical staff, will be immediately snatched, everyone is particularly active. "

He chose to return to the community, where he found a pleasant surprise -- a breakfast restaurant opened in Florida. Duchuan parked his car, bought a favorite local snack in Wuhan "hot dry noodles" , and in his group of drivers to inform you that you can eat hot dry noodles out.

He quickly finished, "eat 10 days of instant noodles, eat a bowl of hot dry noodles too comfortable. "

Du Chuan hasn't had a good meal for a long time. Before the Chinese New Year, his wife and children first went home to Huangpi District, he wanted to pull a few days to live again, did not expect to come to Wuhan News of the closure of the city. On New Year's Eve, he ate the New Year's Eve dinner at home alone, eating salted fish, soy sauce beef and other semi-finished products, and later joined the community convoy, the main food supply is instant noodles.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Photo 3: Du Chuan is checking in at a community service center to pick up demand, photo by Liu Yiqin

Rare so early end, Du Chuan Back to the Community Service Center. The community workers asked him to go to the street to get supplies, a banner used to direct the outbreak, and he rushed over and got a second piece of good news.

A street worker told him that a shipment of vegetables and medical supplies had arrived today, including masks and disinfectant, and that he could sign for them now.

Duchuan was very happy and immediately drove in to carry supplies. The ration of medical supplies, each kind of three boxes, vegetables are "take at will, can load all carry away" , a large bag of cabbage has 12, add up to at least 60 Jin, Du Chuan moved some difficulty, a little while, his protective clothing is full of water vapor.

Back in the community, the community workers sent Duchuan a new batch of supplies, including masks and rubbing alcohol. What was once a common commodity at a bargain price is now a hot commodity. Since there is no separate bottle, sterilizing alcohol in the bottle of mineral water, Du Chuan reminded other caring drivers, "do not confuse as mineral water, turn back into a drunk driving. "

At 9:00 a.m. , another caring driver went to the street to pick up the remaining supplies. When he arrived, the scene was already crowded with vehicles from various communities. Due to the long waiting time, a dispute broke out at the scene. Some people complained loudly about the chaotic process of collecting the car because they did not know whether to wait in line or people, and when they did, they were told that they had not signed it yet. Staff are also very helpless, had to keep apologizing, "we are not in a good mood, mutual understanding of it? "

The caring driver, a native of Xiangyang, Hubei Province, used to do business on his own and chose to be a Didi driver after his business failed. He told Caijing that he felt there was no change in Wuhan now and in the past, "The reality is that it's not as bad as people say, " he said. "It's just that every day the water is sprayed and the seats are a little bit corroded. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Photo 4: Collecting supplies from the street, by Liu Yiqin

February 2,9:20 A.M. : anxious patient

Optimism can not hide the fact that today's Wuhan community has changed greatly. At about 9:20, Du Chuan returned to the community and saw several fever patients coming to the community service center. He asked the community to send a car to the hospital for treatment, but the community security team did not have the protective capacity to transport fever patients. Since January 25, the drivers have worn only one simple protective suit, which has not been replaced.

The patient was upset, had a fever for days, but couldn't go to the hospital, and they said that if they couldn't go to the hospital today, they would sit in the community office. The community workers helped dial 120, were told that all 120 ambulances had been dispatched, and then called 110,110 for details, saying they were too busy to come.

The community staff had to be kind and tell the patient that he had registered and would report it immediately, and that he would be the first to know if there was any news, and the patient eventually chose to go home.

Community workers told Caijing that this happens every day. They receive calls from more than 100 residents asking for help, but "we really don't have the means or the ability. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Photo 5: Community Workers Collate daily traffic demand, by Liu Yiqin

A community worker took out two 3m masks and gave them to the reporter of CAIJING. "We must take them, we can't wear one for a day! " But the reporter found that they were still wearing ordinary medical masks. Because some supplies were scarce, their masks were in short supply. Also, it's important for the community to be well protected from people coming in and coming in with fever from time to time.

In the wake of the outbreak, attention has focused on new pneumonia, with a number of hospitals opening fever clinics or converting wards into isolation rooms for the rising number of infected patients. But there are a lot of other patients in the community, who also need to go to the hospital, or do routine treatment, check-ups, and when all the medical resources are skewed towards new pneumonia, their problems are rarely addressed.

One of the main jobs of caring drivers is to transport dialysis patients to hospitals in the community. It takes four hours to do a dialysis. Sometimes you have to leave early to go to the hospital to get dialysis equipment; sometimes you have to wait until late at night until 12 or 1 a.m.

Du, who lives closest to the community and is also the team leader, tries to do some of the hard work himself, such as using a car after 6 am and 12 pm. Other drivers also admire him, "the captain is not easy, not only to work, but also to organize and coordinate us, anything he rushed in the first. "

"That's leadership, " one driver joked

At 10:50 a.m. , the community workers sorted out the supplies to be distributed to the residents and sent them to a nearby community. Duchuan got the assignment and set off immediately.

This residential area is a commercial housing, residential environment is relatively complex, a floor there are dozens of households, Du Chuan looked for a long time, in advance phone contact residents, one of the residents of the specific address he could not find two circles, the other said can come down to take. The other two residents are not at home at the moment, I hope Duchuan can put materials in the Property Office.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Figure 6 some residential buildings have complex terrain, with dozens of households on the first floor

But the property isn't willing to take over, and at times like these, everyone wants to reduce their exposure. The property staff attitude is not good, put forward must be received by the residents themselves, Duchuan in the Property Office for more than 10 minutes, before the materials to the hands of the residents.

This makes Du Chuan feel some helpless, but he can understand. He urged "finance" reporters, must not touch anything in the community, including door handles, elevator keys, and residents to maintain a distance. He opened the door with his foot, pressed the car key to the elevator, and left everything at the door for the residents to open and get out.

Back in the car, Du Chuan gave himself a simple disinfection. It began to drizzle outside and the temperature began to drop. He said it was time to go back to lunch.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Photo 7: Du Chuan Delivers Home to Resident Liu Yiqin / photo

February 2,2:00 pm: A steady stream of requests for help

In a makeshift lounge in the neighborhood, tables and chairs are haphazardly arranged, there is no air conditioning or heating, and it is raining and getting colder, where drivers eat their lunch.

For lunch, it's not as if there's no choice —— whether it's spicy or not? Wuhan Du Chuan Natural Choice Spicy, "the weather is so cold, a bowl of spicy instant noodles just right. "

Over lunch, the drivers sat down together to talk about their feelings about the outbreak, including the rumors they had heard. The Xiangyang driver said he now has feelings for Wuhan and hopes it will get better soon.

Another driver exclaimed, now do not feel happy days, "one day do not wear a mask, satisfied. "

After lunch, they would take a break in their cars, where it was too cold and drafty, and in their crowded community offices, where they wore protective suits to keep residents from panicking. But in the car also dare not sleep, the temperature is too low, for fear of catching a cold.

Photo 8: Liu Yiqin / Photo of a caring driver during his lunch hour

Du Chuan in the lunch time will continue to pay attention to all kinds of vehicle scheduling information, if there is no arrangement, he will play a "eat chicken" , relax.

But community workers across the street couldn't take a lunch break, and calls were pouring in. An 80 year old empty nester called, saying his fever had reached 38 degrees, couldn't get a nucleic acid test, and asked the community to send a car. Community workers wanted the elderly to provide contact information for their children to help deal with the problem, but the elderly refused to provide it or say why.

A short while later, a young woman came into the community. She wanted to make an appointment for a car service tomorrow. Her sister, a nurse at the Union Medical College, wanted to make a bowl of soup.

Community staff said that occasionally send a few can, but not every day, because drivers and vehicles limited resources, do not waste.

The young woman immediately broke down. "How can you say it's a waste? My sister is on the line. Do you know how hard they work? "

Community officials told Caijing that they also had a hard time, that there were just too many things, like legitimate needs that could be met, and some that they didn't know how to respond to.

For example, a resident called and asked for a dog to be fed and a cat to be delivered immediately. Two days ago, a resident came in, wanted to get a mask, the staff gave him some free medical masks, he turned around to complain that the community to provide poor quality masks.

"We use this mask ourselves, how is it inferior mask, " said a community worker aggrieved.

At 4:30 p.m. on February 2nd, the night shift medics set off

Today is Sunday, "closed city" , the days of the week has become less important, go to the hospital for dialysis patients significantly less. For the medical staff on the front lines, it's still a day of fighting.

At 4:30 pm, a nurse was driven to Liyuan Hospital, the Hubei Provincial Hospital for the elderly, which is now one of the designated hospitals for fever. The nurse, who had booked a community support van for several days in a row, said she was happy and could only ride a shared bike to work during the first few days of the city's closure, although Liyuan hospital is about 4.5 kilometers away from the community and the weather is cold in winter, if it rains, it's still a problem.

Today is the evening shift, she is working in isolation ward, Liyuan hospital has admitted dozens of patients diagnosed with new pneumonia, the Dean has been diagnosed with infection in the hospital.

She told the "Caijing" reporter, the ward has been fully occupied, but every day there are still a large number of fever patients to the outpatient clinic to see a doctor, "most of the patients are not registered

Liyuan hospital materials are also tight, nurses passengers mentioned that a shift is eight hours, according to regulations, four hours to change a protective clothing, but the reality can not do, they can only adhere to a set of equipment for eight hours.

Due to the strain of the ward, it should be one patient in one ward for easy isolation, but now it can only be 2-3 patients in one ward. CAIJING reporter learned that some designated hospitals have admitted six patients to a ward.

"You can only put a mask on a patient 24 hours a day, " the nurse passenger said. "But the good news is that we are in the process of upgrading several other wards so that more beds can be opened up. "

The nurse got off the bus and left. The driver of the bus said, "we picked up a lot of nurses, all young girls, all on the line. It's really not easy. "

At 6 pm, Du Chuan had to take a patient to the hospital for dialysis. The end time was 11:30 pm. After taking the patient to the hospital, he returned home, cooked a meal for himself and rested for a while.

At 11 o'clock, he put on his protective suit, mask and goggles, and set off to pick up the patient from the hospital, the end of the day. Back at home, he also had to disinfect the suit, which had been in use for nine days and was covered in creases, but had to be accompanied through the affected area before new supplies could arrive, escort the next passenger and the next shipment.

As the new-crown pneumonia epidemic continues, all eyes are on Wuhan. There are more and more caring drivers like Duchuan. Not only are companies like Didi and Shouqi organizing, but volunteer teams of voluntary organizations are also getting bigger and bigger. Du Chuan said that the Real front-line is those medical personnel, they are the hardest, "we can do is to do their own, do not complain. "

The Spring Chill in Wuhan is chilly, and the epidemic is still spreading. But also because of the fight against the epidemic, did not know the driver and the doctor, to achieve an unprecedented tacit understanding. "thank you" and "refuels" , is each time they meet and separate the sign.
